This paper is about understanding the representations learned by neural networks, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on comparing the representations learned by two networks with identical architecture but trained from different initializations. This problem is closely related to the field of representation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that aims to learn useful representations of data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
